The function should:
1. Allow expanding and collapsing of rows with details.
2. Toggle selection of rows with checkboxes.
3. Prevent default actions for specific cells.
4. Handle click events on the "Edit" and "Delete" buttons.
5. Prevent row selection when clicking on buttons.

The function should be called with the table ID and an object containing the following properties:
- `details`: A function to render details for a row.
- `buttons`: An object containing functions for "Edit" and "Delete" buttons.
- `checkbox`: A function to handle checkbox selection.

Here is an example of how the function should be called:
```
handleTableInteractions('myTable', {
  details: renderDetails,
  buttons: {
    edit: handleEdit,
    delete: handleDelete
  },
  checkbox: handleCheckbox
});
```

Make sure to include the following HTML elements:
- A checkbox in each row for selection.
- A cell with class "details" for expanding details.
- A cell with class "buttons" for "Edit" and "Delete" buttons.
- A cell with class "actions" for row actions.
- A cell with class "checkbox" for row checkboxes.

Ensure that the function is compatible with modern JavaScript standards and handles edge cases appropriately.

```
function handleTableInteractions(tableId, options) {
  const table = document.getElementById(tableId);
  const rows = table.getElementsByTagName('tr');

  for (let i = 1; i < rows.length; i++) {
    const cells = rows[i].getElementsByTagName('td');
    const checkbox = cells[0].getElementsByTagName('input')[0];
    const detailsCell = cells[1];
    const buttonsCell = cells[2];
    const actionsCell = cells[3];
    const buttonCell = cells[4];

    checkbox.addEventListener('click', function (event) {
      options.checkbox(this, event);
      event.stopPropagation();
    });

    if (detailsCell.innerHTML) {
      const detailsDiv = document.createElement('div');
      detailsDiv.className = 'details';
      detailsDiv.innerHTML = options.details(this);
      rows[i].appendChild(detailsDiv);
      detailsCell.innerHTML = '';
      actionsCell.innerHTML = '<button class="details-btn">Details</button>';

      const detailsBtn = actionsCell.getElementsByTagName('button')[0];
      detailsBtn.addEventListener('click', function (event) {
        const parent = this.parentNode.parentNode;
        const details = parent.getElementsByTagName('div')[0];
        if (details.style.display === 'none') {
          details.style.display = 'block';
        } else {
          details.style.display = 'none';
        }
        event.stopPropagation();
      });
    }

    if (buttonsCell.innerHTML) {
      const editBtn = buttonCell.getElementsByTagName('button')[0];
      editBtn.addEventListener('click', function (event) {
        options.buttons.edit(this, event);
        event.stopPropagation();
      });

      const deleteBtn = buttonCell.getElementsByTagName('button')[1];
      deleteBtn.addEventListener('click', function (event) {
        options.buttons.delete(this, event);
        event.stopPropagation();
      });
    }

    actionsCell.addEventListener('click', function (event) {
      event.stopPropagation();
    });

    if (buttonCell.innerHTML) {
      const editBtn = buttonCell.getElementsByTagName('button')[0];
      const deleteBtn = buttonCell.getElementsByTagName('button')[1];

      editBtn.addEventListener('click', function (event) {
        options.buttons.edit(this, event);
        event.stopPropagation();
      });

      deleteBtn.addEventListener('click', function (event) {
